        <div xml:id="sample1">
            
            <head>THE
CATECHISM,
WITH
Proofs from the New Testament,
and some Additional Questions
and Answers.</head>
            <head>Sect. I. Of the Benefits of BAPTISM.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. WHat is your Name?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. N. or M.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Why <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised> thou<lb/>
tell me the Name <normalised orig="receiv'd" auto="true">received</normalised> in thy Baptism,<lb/>
rather <notvariant>than</notvariant> that of thy Family?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. Because the Name I <normalised orig="receiv'd" auto="true">received</normalised> at my<lb/>
Baptism, puts me in mind of the Duties<lb/>
and <normalised orig="Priviledges" auto="true">Privileges</normalised> of the Christian Religion.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Who gave you this Name?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. My God-fathers and God-mothers in<lb/>
my Baptism; wherein I was made a Member<lb/>
of Christ, the Child of God, and an Inheritor<lb/>
of the Kingdom of Heaven.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            
            <fw type="pageNum">B</fw>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Why did your God-fathers and<lb/>
God-mothers give you your Christian<lb/>
Name?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. Because they presented me to<lb/>
my Baptism, by which I was made a<lb/>
Christian; and did answer, and engage<lb/>
for me; and gave security to the Church<lb/>
for my Christian Education: And therefore<lb/>
I regard them as my Spiritual Parents.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How <normalised orig="wast" auto="true">were</normalised> thou made in Baptism<lb/>
a Member of Christ?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. In being then made a Member<lb/>
of his Spiritual Body, the Church; and<lb/>
thereby united to him as our Head, and<lb/>
deriving from him all my Strength, and<lb/>
Power to live as a Christian.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How is this <normalised orig="prov'd" auto="true">proved</normalised> from Scripture?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From <notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 12.5. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 12.5">We being<lb/>
many, are one Body in Christ.</quote> 
                  <lb/>
1 Cor. 12.12, 13. As <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Cor 12.12-13">the Body is one,<lb/>
and <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> many Members, so also is Christ:<lb/>
For by one Spirit are we all <normalised orig="Baptized" auto="true">Baptised</normalised> into<lb/>
one Body.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Eph</notvariant>. 1.22, 23 <quote type="biblical" ana="Eph 1.22-23">He gave him to be the<lb/>
head over all things to the Church, Which<lb/>
is his Body.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How <normalised orig="wast" auto="true">were</normalised> thou made in Baptism<lb/>
the Child of God?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. In being then by the Grace,<lb/>
and favour of God adopted for one of<lb/>
his Children; through Christ, and our<lb/>
regeneration in him.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How is this <normalised orig="prov'd" auto="true">proved</normalised> from Scripture?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From <notvariant>Joh</notvariant>. 1.12. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 1.12">As many as<lb/>
received him, to them gave he power to become<lb/>
the Sons of God, even to them that<lb/>
believe on his Name.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 8.15. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 8.15"><normalised orig="Ye" auto="true">You</normalised> have received the Spirit<lb/>
of adoption, whereby we cry, <notvariant>Abba</notvariant>,<lb/>
Father.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Gal. 3.26, 27. <quote type="biblical" ana="Gal 3.26-27"><normalised orig="Ye" auto="true">You</normalised> are all the Children<lb/>
of God by faith in Christ Jesus: For as<lb/>
many of you as have been <normalised orig="baptized" auto="true">baptised</normalised> into<lb/>
Christ, have put on Christ.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How <normalised orig="wast" auto="true">were</normalised> thou made in Baptism<lb/>
an Inheritor of the Kingdom of<lb/>
Heaven? <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. In having the promise of this<lb/>
Eternal Inheritance; so that I may surely<lb/>
attain to it, by leading a Christian life.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How is this <normalised orig="prov'd" auto="true">proved</normalised> from Scripture?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Luke 12.32. <quote type="biblical" ana="Lk 12.32">Fear not,<lb/>
                     <lb/>
                    <fw type="pageNum">B2</fw>
                     <pb n="3"/>
                     <lb/>
little Flock; for it is your Father's good<lb/>
pleasure to give you the Kingdom.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 8.16, 17. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 8.16-17">We are the Children of<lb/>
God; And if Children, then Heirs, Heirs<lb/>
of God, and <normalised orig="Joynt-heirs" auto="false">Joint-heirs</normalised> with Christ.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Tit. 3.5, 7. <quote type="biblical" ana="Titus 3.5">According to his mercy he<lb/>
saved us, by the washing of regeneration, and<lb/>
renewing of the Holy Ghost</quote>: <quote type="biblical" ana="Titus 3.7">That being<lb/>
justified by his Grace, we should be made<lb/>
Heirs according to the hope of eternal Life.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 John 2.25. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 2.25">This is the promise that<lb/>
he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> <normalised orig="promis'd" auto="true">promised</normalised> us, even eternal Life.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
        </div>
         <div>
            <head>SECT. II. Of the Vow of Baptism.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. YOu have told me what you<lb/>
were made in Baptism: but<lb/>
cannot you forfeit these great advantages?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I cannot fail of them, if I keep<lb/>
the Promises made for me, when I was<lb/>
<normalised orig="baptiz'd" auto="true">baptised</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What did your God-fathers and<lb/>
God-mothers then for you?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. They did promise, and vow three things<lb/>
in my Name: First, that I should renounce<lb/>
the Devil, and all his works; the <normalised orig="pomps" auto="false">pumps</normalised>, and<lb/>
vanity of this wicked World; and all the sinful<lb/>
lusts of the Flesh. Secondly, that I should<lb/>
believe all the <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>*r*les</sic>
                     <corr>Articles</corr>
                  </choice> of the Christian Faith.<lb/>
                  <pb n="4"/>
                  <lb/>
And thirdly, that I should keep God's holy Will,<lb/>
and Commandments; and walk in the same all<lb/>
the days of my life. <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. <normalised orig="Dost" auto="true">Do</normalised> thou not think, that thou art<lb/>
bound to believe, and to do, as they have promised<lb/>
for thee?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. Yes verily; and by God's help so I<lb/>
will. And I heartily thank our heavenly <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>F*<notvariant>ther</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>Father</corr>
                  </choice>,<lb/>
that he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> called me to this state of salvation,<lb/>
through <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised> Christ our Saviour. And<lb/>
I pray unto God, to give me his Grace, that I<lb/>
may continue in the same unto my lives end.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Thou <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised> well in praying to<lb/>
God for his Grace, and in owning the<lb/>
necessity of his help: But what Proof<lb/>
<normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou from Scripture, for the doing so?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From John 15.5. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 15.5">Without me <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised><lb/>
can do nothing.</quote>
                  <lb/>
2 Cor. 12.9. <quote type="biblical" ana="2 Cor 12.9">He said unto me, My<lb/>
Grace is sufficient for thee; for my strength<lb/>
is made perfect in weakness.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Phil. 2.13. <quote type="biblical" ana="Phil 2.13">It is God which <normalised orig="worketh" auto="true">works</normalised> in<lb/>
you, both to will, and to do, of his good<lb/>
pleasure.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Phil. 4.13. <quote type="biblical" ana="Phil 4.13">I can do all things through<lb/>
Christ, which <normalised orig="strengthneth" auto="true">strengthens</normalised> me.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Where <normalised orig="didst" auto="true">did</normalised> thou learn to pray<lb/>
to God for his Grace?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Luke 11.13. <quote type="biblical" ana="Lk 11.13">If <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> being<lb/>
                     <lb/>
                    <fw type="pageNum">B3</fw>
                     <pb n="5"/>
                     <lb/>
evil, know how to give good gifts unto your<lb/>
Children; how much more shall your heavenly<lb/>
Father, give the holy Spirit to them<lb/>
that ask him?</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Heb</notvariant>. 4.16. <quote type="biblical" ana="Heb 4.16">Let us come boldly unto the<lb/>
Throne of Grace; that we may obtain mercy,<lb/>
and find Grace to help in time of need. </quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised> thou bind thy self to,<lb/>
in renouncing the Devil, and all his works?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I bind my self to the abhorrence of<lb/>
Satan, and all his temptations; and to the<lb/>
avoiding of all wickedness, either prompted<lb/>
by him, or done in imitation of him.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of this<lb/>
Obligation? <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From 1 John 3.8. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 3.8">He that <normalised orig="committeth" auto="true">commits</normalised><lb/>
Sin is of the Devil; for the Devil<lb/>
<normalised orig="sinneth" auto="true">sins</normalised> from the beginning: For this purpose<lb/>
the Son of God was manifested, that he<lb/>
might destroy the works of the Devil.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 John 5.18. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 5.18">We know that whosoever<lb/>
is born of God, <normalised orig="sinneth" auto="true">sins</normalised> not: But he that is<lb/>
begotten of God, <normalised orig="keepeth" auto="true">keeps</normalised> himself; and that<lb/>
wicked one <normalised orig="toucheth" auto="true">touches</normalised> him not.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Ephes</notvariant>. 4.27. <quote type="biblical" ana="Eph 4.27">Neither give place to the<lb/>
Devil.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised> thou bind thy self<lb/>
to, in renouncing the <notvariant>pomps</notvariant> and vanity<lb/>
of this wicked World?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="6"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I bind my self not to seek greedily,<lb/>
or by unlawful means, after Honour,<lb/>
and Glory, and Riches; nor to use any of<lb/>
God's Creatures to excess; but to refrain<lb/>
from Pride, and Ambition, and Covetousness;<lb/>
and from ungodly and vain Customs,<lb/>
and all the outward <notvariant>allurements</notvariant> to Sin.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of this<lb/>
Obligation?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From 1 John 2.15. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 2.15">Love not the<lb/>
World, neither the things that are in the<lb/>
World. If any Man love the World, the love<lb/>
of the Father is not in him.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 12.2. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 12.2">Be not conformed to this<lb/>
World.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Jam. 4.4. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jas 4.4">Know <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> not, that the friendship<lb/>
of the World is enmity with God?<lb/>
Whosoever therefore will be a friend of the<lb/>
World, is the enemy of God.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised> thou bind thy self to,<lb/>
in renouncing the sinful lusts of the Flesh?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I bind my self to abstain from<lb/>
those sensual Pleasures, which God <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised><lb/>
forbidden; and to resist all impure desires;<lb/>
and to tame, and regulate my disorderly<lb/>
Inclinations, and corrupt Nature,<lb/>
inwardly delighting in what is evil.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of this<lb/>
Obligation?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            
            <fw type="pageNum">B4</fw>
            <pb n="7"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Gal. 5.24. <quote type="biblical" ana="Gal 5.24">They that are<lb/>
Christ's have crucified the Flesh, with the<lb/>
affections, and lusts.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 8.13. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 8.13">If <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> live after the Flesh, <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised><lb/>
shall die: but if <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> through the spirit do <normalised orig="mortifie" auto="true">mortify</normalised><lb/>
the deeds of the Body, <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> shall live.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 Pet. 2.11. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Pet 2.11">I beseech you as Strangers,<lb/>
and Pilgrims, abstain from fleshly lusts,<lb/>
which war against the Soul.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of being<lb/>
bound to believe all the Articles of the<lb/>
Christian Faith?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From John 3.36. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 3.36">He that <normalised orig="believeth" auto="true">believes</normalised><lb/>
on the Son, <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> everlasting life: and<lb/>
he that <normalised orig="believeth" auto="true">believes</normalised> not the Son, shall not see<lb/>
life; but the wrath of God <normalised orig="abideth" auto="true">abides</normalised> on him.</quote>
                  <lb/>
John 17.3. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 17.3">This is life eternal, that<lb/>
they might know thee the only true God, and<lb/>
Jesus Christ whom thou <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> sent.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Mar. 16.16. <quote type="biblical" ana="Mk 16.16">He that <normalised orig="believeth" auto="true">believes</normalised>, and is<lb/>
<normalised orig="baptized" auto="true">baptised</normalised>, shall be saved: but he that <normalised orig="believeth" auto="true">believes</normalised><lb/>
not, shall be damned.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 John 3.23. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 3.23">This is his commandment,<lb/>
that we should believe on the Name of his<lb/>
Son Jesus Christ.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of being<lb/>
bound to keep all the Commandments of<lb/>
God?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="8"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From John 14.15. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 14.15">If <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> love<lb/>
me, keep my Commandments.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Mat. 28.20. <quote type="biblical" ana="Mt 28.20">Teaching them to observe<lb/>
all things, whatsoever I have commanded you.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 John 2.3.4. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 2.3-4">Hereby we do know that<lb/>
we know him, if we keep his Commandments.<lb/>
He that saith, I know him, and <normalised orig="keepeth" auto="true">keeps</normalised><lb/>
not his Commandments, is a liar, and the<lb/>
truth is not in him.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Eph</notvariant>. 2.10. <quote type="biblical" ana="Eph 2.10">We are his Workmanship,<lb/>
created in Christ Jesus unto good works,<lb/>
which God <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> before ordained, that we<lb/>
should walk in them.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div>
            <head>SECT. III. Of the Creed: and more particularly
of God the Father.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p><notvariant>Catechist</notvariant>. Rehearse the Articles of thy Belief.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>.  I Believe in God the Father Almighty,<lb/>
Maker of Heaven, and<lb/>
Earth:  And in <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised> Christ, his only Son,<lb/>
our Lord:  Who was Conceived by the Holy<lb/>
Ghost, Born of the <normalised orig="Uirgin" auto="true">Virgin</normalised> Mary:  Suffered<lb/>
under <notvariant>Pontius</notvariant> Pilate; was Crucified, Dead,<lb/>
and Buried; He descended into Hell:  The<lb/>
third day he rose again from the dead:  He<lb/>
ascended into Heaven, and <normalised orig="sitteth" auto="true">sits</normalised> at the right-hand<lb/>
of God the Father Almighty.  From<lb/>
thence he shall come to judge the Quick, and the<lb/>
                  <pb n="9"/>
                  <lb/>
Dead.  I believe in the Holy Ghost:  The<lb/>
Holy <normalised orig="Catholick" auto="true">Catholic</normalised> Church, the Communion of<lb/>
Saints:  The forgiveness of <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>Sin*</sic>
                     <corr>Sins</corr>
                  </choice>: <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>T*</sic>
                     <corr>The</corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
Resurrection of the Body:  And the Life<lb/>
Everlasting. Amen.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Thou <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> well repeated this<lb/>
Apostolical Summary of the Principles of<lb/>
the Christian Religion: But why <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised><lb/>
thou say Amen, after the rehearsing of it?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. To <normalised orig="testifie" auto="true">testify</normalised> my <normalised orig="stedfast" auto="true">steadfast</normalised> belief of<lb/>
it; and my desire to live, as one that<lb/>
heartily believes it.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised> thou chiefly learn in<lb/>
these Articles of thy <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>B*l*</sic>
                     <corr>Belief</corr>
                  </choice>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. First, I learn to believe in God the<lb/>
Father, who <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> made me, and all the World.<lb/>
Secondly, In God the Son, who <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> redeemed<lb/>
me, and all Mankind.<lb/>
Thirdly, In God the Holy Ghost; who<lb/>
<normalised orig="sanctifieth" auto="false">sanctifies</normalised> me, and all the <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>El*<notvariant>ct</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>Elect</corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>P*<notvariant>ple</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>People</corr>
                  </choice> of God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What is it to believe in God?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. To believe that God is, and that<lb/>
he is faithful, and true in all his words:<lb/>
and to trust in him, and depend upon him.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>
                  <lb/>
                  <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>Q*</sic>
                     <corr>Quest.</corr>
                  </choice> Let us go over the Articles of<lb/>
the Creed more distinctly: What <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><notvariant>beli</notvariant>*est</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised></corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
thou concerning the first Article,<lb/>
I believe in God the Father Almighty, Maker<lb/>
of Heaven, and Earth?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I believe that there is one living,<lb/>
                  <pb n="10"/>
                  <lb/>
and true God; an Infinite, Eternal,<lb/>
and Incomprehensible Spirit; having all<lb/>
Perfections in, and of himself: and that<lb/>
God was from all Eternity the Father of<lb/>
our Lord Christ; and that he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> an<lb/>
unlimited Power, and Right to do whatsoever<lb/>
he <normalised orig="pleaseth" auto="true">pleases</normalised>; and that he did exert<lb/>
this Power in making out of nothing, by<lb/>
his Word alone, the Heavens, and the<lb/>
Earth, and all things therein; which he<lb/>
still preserves, and <normalised orig="disposeth" auto="true">disposes</normalised> of most<lb/>
wisely, according to his own Will.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of God's<lb/>
being an Eternal Spirit?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From John 4.24. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 4.24">God is a Spirit.</quote>
                  <lb/>
