         <div>
            <head>SECT. IV. Of Christ in his Divine
Nature, and Incarnation.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. WHat <normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised> thou concerning<lb/>
the second Article<lb/>
of the Creed, And in Jesus Christ,<lb/>
his only Son, our Lord?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I believe in Jesus, as the Saviour<lb/>
of Mankind; and that he is truly the<lb/>
Christ, who was promised to come for our<lb/>
Redemption: and that he is the only Son<lb/>
of God by Nature, begotten from everlasting<lb/>
                  <pb n="13"/>
                  <lb/>
of the Father: and that he is our<lb/>
Lord, and Master, and God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What is <normalised orig="imply'd" auto="true">implied</normalised> by owning<lb/>
Jesus to be Christ, or the <notvariant>Messias</notvariant>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. That he was the promised Redeemer<lb/>
of his People; and was anointed<lb/>
with the Spirit of God, to be their<lb/>
King, and Priest, and Prophet.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How is Christ our King, and<lb/>
Priest, and Prophet?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. He is our King, in governing,<lb/>
and protecting his Church: He is our<lb/>
Priest, in offering one Sacrifice, and always<lb/>
interceding for us: and he is our<lb/>
Prophet, in teaching us most perfectly<lb/>
the Will of God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of being<lb/>
bound to <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>*<notvariant>elieve</notvariant></sic>
                     <corr>believe</corr>
                  </choice> in Christ?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From John 3.18. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 3.18">He that <normalised orig="believeth" auto="true">believes</normalised><lb/>
on him, is not condemned: but he<lb/>
that <normalised orig="believeth" auto="true">believes</normalised> not, is condemned already;<lb/>
because he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> not believed in the Name of<lb/>
the only begotten Son of God.</quote>
                  <lb/>
John 14.1. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 14.1"><normalised orig="Ye" auto="true">You</normalised> believe in God; believe<lb/>
also in me.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Acts 16.31. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 16.31">Believe on the Lord Jesus<lb/>
Christ, and thou shalt be saved.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="14"/>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised> thou prove, that<lb/>
Christ is the Saviour of Mankind?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Mat. 1.21. <quote type="biblical" ana="Mt 1.21">Thou shalt call<lb/>
his Name Jesus: for he shall save his People<lb/>
from their Sins.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 Tim. 1.15. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Tim 1.15">This a faithful saying,<lb/>
and worthy of all <normalised orig="acceptation" auto="true">acceptance</normalised>; That Christ<lb/>
