                  <lb/>
Phil. 2.6. <quote type="biblical" ana="Phil 2.6">Who being in the form of God,<lb/>
thought it not Robbery to be <choice ana="illegible">
                        <sic><notvariant>equ</notvariant>*l</sic>
                        <corr>equal</corr>
                     </choice> with God.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Col 2.9. <quote type="biblical" ana="Col 2.9">In him <normalised orig="dwelleth" auto="true">dwells</normalised> all the <normalised orig="fulness" auto="false">fullness</normalised><lb/>
of the <normalised orig="Godhead" auto="false">Godhood</normalised> bodily.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised> thou concerning<lb/>
the third Article of the Creed,<lb/>
Who was Conceived by the Holy Ghost,<lb/>
Born of the Virgin Mary?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I believe that Christ was Conceived<lb/>
without any Sin, by the miraculous<lb/>
Power of the Holy Ghost over-shadowing<lb/>
a pure Virgin, whose Name<lb/>
was Mary: and that he perfectly took<lb/>
our Nature, and was born of her, appearing<lb/>
hereby to be the Son of David.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of our<lb/>
