         </div>
         <div>
            <head>SECT. V. Of Christ in his Sufferings,
and Exaltation.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. WHat <normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised> thou concerning<lb/>
the fourth Article<lb/>
of the Creed, Suffered under <notvariant>Pontius</notvariant> Pilate,<lb/>
was Crucified, Dead, and<lb/>
Buried; He descended into<lb/>
Hell? <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I believe that the<lb/>
Son of God having taken<lb/>
our Flesh, did therein, for<lb/>
our benefit, undergo the accursed<lb/>
death of the Cross; to which<lb/>
he was condemned by <notvariant>Pontius</notvariant> Pilate,<lb/>
the Roman <normalised orig="Governour" auto="true">Governor</normalised> of <notvariant>Judea</notvariant>: and<lb/>
that his Soul was really separated from<lb/>
his Body; which lying for some time in<lb/>
the Grave, his Soul removed to the Spirits<lb/>
of Men departed; and having <normalised orig="conquer'd" auto="true">conquered</normalised><lb/>
the Powers of Darkness by his<lb/>
Cross, he went down into Hell.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            
            <fw type="pageNum">C2</fw>
            <pb n="19"/>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Why did our Lord submit to<lb/>
the death of the Cross?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. To deliver Mankind, by the infinite<lb/>
price of his Blood, from the Punishment,<lb/>
and Curse that was due for<lb/>
our Sins; and to reconcile his Father to<lb/>
us, by satisfying his Justice, and making<lb/>
himself a Sacrifice for us.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How is this end of our Saviour's<lb/>
death <normalised orig="prov'd" auto="true">proved</normalised> from the Scripture?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Gal. 3.13. <quote type="biblical" ana="Gal 3.13">Christ <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised><lb/>
redeemed us from the Curse of the Law, being<lb/>
made a Curse for us.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Rom</notvariant> 5 10. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 5.10">When we were Enemies, we<lb/>
were reconciled to God by the death of his Son.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 Pet. 2.24. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Pet 2.24">Who his own self bare our<lb/>
sins in his own Body on the Tree, that we being<lb/>
dead to Sins, should live unto Righteousness:<lb/>
by whose Stripes <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> were healed.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 John 2.2. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 2.2">He is the propitiation for<lb/>
our Sins: and not for ours only, but also for<lb/>
the Sins of the whole World.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof is there of Christ's<lb/>
descending into Hell?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Acts 2.25, 27. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 2.25">David<lb/>
<normalised orig="speaketh" auto="true">speaks</normalised> concerning him</quote>, <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 2.27">Thou wilt not<lb/>
leave my Soul in Hell.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised> thou concerning<lb/>
                  <pb n="20"/>
                  <lb/>
the fifth Article of the Creed, The<lb/>
third day he rose again from the dead?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I believe that on the Morning<lb/>
of the third day after his Passion, the<lb/>
Soul of Christ was united again to his<lb/>
<normalised orig="crucify'd" auto="true">crucified</normalised> Body; and he arose from the<lb/>
Grave, to an Immortal Life, by the<lb/>
Power of God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How <normalised orig="dost" auto="true">do</normalised> thou prove the Resurrection<lb/>
of Christ in this manner?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From the History of the Gospel:<lb/>
and from<lb/>
Acts 2.24. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 2.24">Whom God <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> raised up,<lb/>
having loosed the pains of Death; because it<lb/>
was not possible, that he should be holden of it.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Acts 13.37. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 13.37">He whom God raised again,<lb/>
saw no corruption.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 6.9. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 6.9">Christ being raised from the<lb/>
dead, <normalised orig="dieth" auto="true">dies</normalised> no more; Death <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> no more<lb/>
dominion over him.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Rev. 1.18. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rev 1.18">I am he that <normalised orig="liveth" auto="true">lives</normalised>, and<lb/>
was dead: and behold, I am alive for evermore,<lb/>
Amen; and have the Keys of Hell,<lb/>
and of Death.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised> thou concerning<lb/>
the sixth Article of the Creed, He<lb/>
ascended into Heaven; and <normalised orig="sitteth" auto="true">sits</normalised> at the<lb/>
right hand of God the Father Almighty?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            
            <fw type="pageNum">C3</fw>
            <pb n="21"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I believe that Christ, having<lb/>
<normalised orig="finish'd" auto="true">finished</normalised> by his death the work of our<lb/>
Redemption, was in his <normalised orig="glorify'd" auto="false">glorified</normalised> Body<lb/>
taken up to Heaven, in the sight of his<lb/>
Disciples, forty days after his Resurrection:<lb/>
and that from his entrance into<lb/>
Heaven, he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> been exalted to the<lb/>
honour of sitting at the right hand of<lb/>
God the Father; and of appearing for us<lb/>
in his Presence, with full Power, and<lb/>
Dominion.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Thou <normalised orig="didst" auto="true">did</normalised> tell me truly, that<lb/>
God is a Spirit; and how then can Christ<lb/>
sit at his right hand?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. This Expression is <normalised orig="borrow'd" auto="true">borrowed</normalised><lb/>
from the manner of Men, in counting<lb/>
it the most honourable place, to be set<lb/>
on the right hand of a Prince: and so<lb/>
it signifies, that Christ is <normalised orig="advanc'd" auto="true">advanced</normalised> in<lb/>
Heaven to the highest Dignity, and<lb/>
Authority under God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of the<lb/>
truth of this Article?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From the History of our Lord's<lb/>
Ascension: and from<lb/>
1 Pet. 3.22. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Pet 3.22">Who is gone into Heaven,<lb/>
and is on the right hand of God;<lb/>
Angels, and Authorities, and Powers being<lb/>
made subject unto him.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <pb n="22"/>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Eph</notvariant>. 1.20, 21. <quote type="biblical" ana="Eph 1.20-21">He raised him from the<lb/>
dead, and set him at his own right hand in<lb/>
the heavenly places; Far above all Principality,<lb/>
and Power, and Might, and Dominion;<lb/>
and every name that is named, not only in this<lb/>
World, but also in that which is to come.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Heb</notvariant>. 10.12. <quote type="biblical" ana="Heb 10.12">This Man after he had<lb/>
offered one sacrifice for sins, for ever sat<lb/>
down on the right hand of God.</quote> 
                  <lb/>
Acts 7.56. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 7.56">Behold, I see the Heavens<lb/>
opened, and the Son of Man standing on the<lb/>
right hand of God.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised> thou concerning<lb/>
the seventh Article of the Creed,<lb/>
                  <lb/>
From thence he shall come to <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>j*e</sic>
                     <corr>judge</corr>
                  </choice> the<lb/>
                  <lb/>
Quick, and the Dead?<lb/>
