         <div>
            <head>SECT. VI. Of the Holy Ghost: and the
following Articles of the Creed.</head>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. WHat <normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised> thou concerning<lb/>
the eighth Article<lb/>
of the Creed, I believe in the Holy Ghost?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I believe in the Holy Spirit, as<lb/>
God, together with the Father, and the<lb/>
Son: and that as the Scriptures come<lb/>
from his Inspiration; so by his working<lb/>
upon the Soul, all good Christians are<lb/>
                  <pb n="24"/>
                  <lb/>
led, and converted, and <normalised orig="sanctify'd" auto="true">sanctified</normalised>, and<lb/>
made acceptable to God.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of these<lb/>
operations of the Divine Spirit?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From <notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 8.14. <quote type="biblical" ana="Rom 8.14">As many as<lb/>
are led by the Spirit of God, they are the<lb/>
Sons of God.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 Cor. 3.16. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Cor 3.16">Know <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> not that <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> are<lb/>
the Temple of God; and that the Spirit of<lb/>
God <normalised orig="dwelleth" auto="true">dwells</normalised> in you?</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 Cor. 6.11. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Cor 6.11">But <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> are washed, but<lb/>
<normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> are sanctified, but <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> are justified in the<lb/>
name of the Lord Jesus, and by the Spirit<lb/>
of our God.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 John 4.13. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 4.13">Hereby know we that we<lb/>
dwell in him, and he in us, because he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised><lb/>
given us of his Spirit.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou, that<lb/>
the Scriptures come from the Inspiration<lb/>
of the Holy Ghost?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From 2 Tim. 3.16. <quote type="biblical" ana="2 Tim 3.16">All Scripture<lb/>
is given by inspiration of God?</quote> 
                  <lb/>
2 Pet. 1.21. <quote type="biblical" ana="2 Pet 1.21">The Prophecy came not in<lb/>
old time by the Will of Man: but holy Men<lb/>
of God <normalised orig="spake" auto="true">spoke</normalised>, as they were moved by the<lb/>
Holy Ghost.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Acts 3.21. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 3.21">God <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> spoken by the<lb/>
mouth of all his holy Prophets, since the<lb/>
World began.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <pb n="25"/>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Joh</notvariant>. 16.13. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 16.13">When he the Spirit of Truth<lb/>
is come, he will guide you into all truth.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="believest" auto="true">believe</normalised> thou concerning<lb/>
the ninth Article of the Creed, The Holy<lb/>
<normalised orig="Catholick" auto="true">Catholic</normalised> Church, the Communion of Saints?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. I believe that the Servants of<lb/>
God in all ages, and places, have made<lb/>
up one Body under Christ their Head;<lb/>
and that there is, and always will be a<lb/>
company of true Believers, appointed to<lb/>
Salvation, and <normalised orig="joyning" auto="true">joining</normalised> in the Word, and<lb/>
Sacraments under Pastors lawfully <normalised orig="ordain'd" auto="true">ordained</normalised>:<lb/>
and that the Members of this<lb/>
Church are called to be Saints; and<lb/>
ought to maintain communion with<lb/>
Christ, and fellowship with one another<lb/>
in all the Offices of Piety, and Charity.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. Why is the Church called Holy,<lb/>
and <normalised orig="Catholick" auto="true">Catholic</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. The Church is called Holy,<lb/>
because <normalised orig="'tis" auto="true">it is</normalised> <normalised orig="joyned" auto="true">joined</normalised> to God in Covenant;<lb/>
and the true Members of it are <normalised orig="sanctify'd" auto="true">sanctified</normalised><lb/>
by the Spirit of Holiness: and <normalised orig="'tis" auto="true">it is</normalised> called<lb/>
<normalised orig="Catholick" auto="true">Catholic</normalised>, or Universal because <normalised orig="'tis" auto="true">it is</normalised> spread<lb/>
over all the World, and all Nations are<lb/>
equally admitted to it.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of this Holy,<lb/>
<normalised orig="Catholick" auto="true">Catholic</normalised> Church?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <pb n="26"/>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Mat. 16.18. <quote type="biblical" ana="Mt 16.18"><normalised orig="Vpon" auto="true">Upon</normalised> this<lb/>
Rock I will build my Church; and the Gates<lb/>
of Hell shall not prevail against it.</quote> 
                  <lb/>
Acts 20.28. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 20.28">The Holy Ghost <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> made<lb/>
you Overseers, to feed the Church of God,<lb/>
which he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> purchased with his own blood.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Mar. 16.15. <quote type="biblical" ana="Mk 16.15">Go <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> into all the World,<lb/>
and preach the Gospel to every creature.</quote>
                  <lb/>
<notvariant>Eph</notvariant>. 5.27. <quote type="biblical" ana="Eph 5.27">That he might present it to<lb/>
himself a <choice ana="illegible">
                        <sic>*l*</sic>
                        <corr>glorious</corr>
                     </choice> Church, <choice ana="illegible">
                        <sic>*t</sic>
                        <corr>not</corr>
                     </choice> having spot,<lb/>
or wrinkle: but that it should be holy, and<lb/>
without blemish.</quote>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. What Proof <normalised orig="hast" auto="true">have</normalised> thou of the<lb/>
Communion of Saints?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Acts 2.42. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 2.42">They continued<lb/>
<normalised orig="stedfastly" auto="true">steadfastly</normalised> in the Apostles doctrine, and fellowship;<lb/>
