penitent Sinners, and sealed in Baptism,<lb/>
through the Merits of our Saviour's<lb/>
Death, and Satisfaction: and that he<lb/>
<normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> <normalised orig="authoriz'd" auto="true">authorised</normalised> the Ministers of his<lb/>
Church, to declare, and apply this release<lb/>
from the guilt of Sin, to all such as<lb/>
sincerely believe, and repent. <lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How is this <normalised orig="prov'd" auto="true">proved</normalised> from Scripture?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From Luke 24.47. <quote type="biblical" ana="Lk 24.47">That repentance,<lb/>
and remission of sins should be<lb/>
preached in his name among all Nations.</quote>
                  <lb/>
2 Cor. 5.19. <quote type="biblical" ana="2 Cor 5.19">God was in Christ, reconciling<lb/>
the World unto himself, not imputing<lb/>
their trespasses unto them; and <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised><lb/>
