            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How is this <normalised orig="prov'd" auto="true">proved</normalised> from Scripture?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From John 5.28, 29. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 5.28-29">The hour<lb/>
is coming, in the which all that are in the<lb/>
Graves shall hear his voice, And shall come<lb/>
forth; they that have done good, unto the resurrection<lb/>
of Life; and they that have done<lb/>
evil, unto the resurrection of Damnation.</quote>
                  <lb/>
Acts 24.15. <quote type="biblical" ana="Acts 24.15">I <choice ana="illegible">
                        <sic>h*<notvariant>ve</notvariant></sic>
                        <corr>have</corr>
                     </choice> hope towards God,<lb/>
which they themselves also allow, that there<lb/>
shall be a resurrection of the dead, both of the<lb/>
