            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Quest. How is this <normalised orig="prov'd" auto="true">proved</normalised> from Scripture?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p><notvariant>Answ</notvariant>. From John 6.47. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 6.47">Verily, verily<lb/>
I say unto you; He that <normalised orig="believeth" auto="true">believes</normalised> on me,<lb/>
<normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> everlasting life.</quote>
                  <lb/>
John 10.28. <quote type="biblical" ana="Jn 10.28">I give unto them eternal<lb/>
life; and they shall never perish, neither<lb/>
shall any pluck them out of my hand.</quote>
                  <lb/>
1 Pet. 5.4. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Pet 5.4">When the chief Shepherd<lb/>
shall appear, <normalised orig="ye" auto="true">you</normalised> shall receive a Crown of glory<lb/>
that <normalised orig="fadeth" auto="true">fades</normalised> not away.</quote> 
                  <lb/>
1 John 5.11. <quote type="biblical" ana="1 Jn 5.11">This is the record, that<lb/>
God <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> given to us eternal life: and this<lb/>
